{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2018/04/02/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"kilimchoi/engineering-blogs","categoryHTML":"<h4>C companies</h4>","itemHTML":"<li>Condé Nast <a href=\"https://technology.condenast.com/\">https://technology.condenast.com/</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T21:17:03.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"woop/awesome-quantified-self","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications and Platforms</h2><h3>Goals</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.taskade.com/\">Taskade</a> - Simple and sharable tasks, checklists, and notes. (Web, iOS &#x26; Android).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T19:15:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mislavcimpersak/awesome-dev-fun","categoryHTML":"<h2>Esoteric languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/molnarmark/onlytoday\">OnlyToday</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/molnarmark/onlytoday\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6,\"repo\":\"molnarmark/onlytoday\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A date and time based programming language.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T16:49:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"transitive-bullshit/awesome-ffmpeg","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leandromoreira/ffmpeg-libav-tutorial\">Learn FFmpeg libav the Hard Way</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/leandromoreira/ffmpeg-libav-tutorial\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8180,\"repo\":\"leandromoreira/ffmpeg-libav-tutorial\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T15:00:49.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Blog posts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@sjbarbeau/gtfs-best-practices-now-available-88ac67194233\">\"GTFS Best Practices now available!\" by Sean Barbeau</a> - Discusses some of the challenges of an open data format like GTFS and the GTFS Best Practices that were launched in early 2017 to help address data quality.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:48:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0968090X12000022\">Tang et al. - \"Ridership effects of real-time bus information system: A case study in the City of Chicago\"</a> - Experiment in Chicago, IL showed modest increase in ridership when riders had access to real-time info via text message or email.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:45:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://faculty.washington.edu/jhullman/busUncertaintyVis.pdf\">Kay et al. - \"When(ish) is my bus? User-centered Visualizations of Uncertainty in Everyday, Mobile Predictive Systems\"</a> - Paper attempts to answr the question of \"how do we communicate uncertainty in transit predictions?\" Explains the problem, existing solutions and designs a <a href=\"https://github.com/mjskay/when-ish-is-my-bus/blob/master/quantile-dotplots.md#quantile-dotplots\">better interface for letting users know when to arrive at the bus stop</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:45:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0965856411001030\">Watkins et al. - \"Where Is My Bus? Impact of mobile real-time information on the perceived and actual wait time of transit riders\"</a> - Experiments in Seattl,e WA showed that riders perceived shorter bus wait times when they had access to real-time info via mobile apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:45:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0965856414002146\">Brakewood et al. - “An experiment evaluating the impacts of real-time transit information on bus riders in Tampa, Florida”</a> - Controlled experiment in Tampa, FL showed that riders with access to real-time info via mobile apps perceived nearly 2 minute reduction in wait times compared to riders without real-time info.  Riders with real-time info also had decreases in anxiety and frustration and better reception of agency.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:45:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0968090X15000297\">Brakewood et al. - \"The impact of real-time information on bus ridership in New York City\"</a> - Experiment in NYC showed that ridership increased on long routes when real-time info was made available to riders.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:45:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"transitive-bullshit/awesome-ffmpeg","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-probe\">ffmpeg-probe</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-probe\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10,\"repo\":\"transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-probe\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Wrapper around ffprobe for getting info about media files.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:43:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"transitive-bullshit/awesome-ffmpeg","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-frame\">ffmpeg-extract-frame</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-frame\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":13,\"repo\":\"transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-frame\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Extracts a single frame from a video.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:43:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"transitive-bullshit/awesome-ffmpeg","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-audio\">ffmpeg-extract-audio</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-audio\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"transitive-bullshit/ffmpeg-extract-audio\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Extracts an audio stream from a media file.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:43:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>3rd party GTFS URL directories</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.gtfs-data-exchange.com/agencies\"><del>GTFS Data Exchange</del> (Deprecated)</a> - Formerly the definitive directory of GTFS feed URLs. Shutdown in 2016. But 93 GB of data from 2008 to 2016 is available upon request.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Transit agency data archives</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/scascketta/CapMetrics\">CapMetrics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/scascketta/CapMetrics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15,\"repo\":\"scascketta/CapMetrics\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Historical vehicle locations for Austin's transit agency (CapMetro). Data is collected by <a href=\"https://github.com/scascketta/capmetricsd\">capmetricsd</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/scascketta/capmetricsd\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10,\"repo\":\"scascketta/capmetricsd\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, a Go daemon.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Proprietary (non-standard) vendor APIs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.transportapi.com/\">Transport API</a> - REST API for aggregated transit data for the United Kingdom.  Fee-based access.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Proprietary (non-standard) vendor APIs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://market.mashape.com/transloc/openapi-1-2\">TransLoc OpenAPI</a> - REST API for real-time vehicle, route, stop, and arrival data for over 60 transit systems in the United States that have purchased TransLoc's AVL hardware and software.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Proprietary (non-standard) vendor APIs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.nextbus.com/xmlFeedDocs/NextBusXMLFeed.pdf\">NextBus API</a> - REST API for real-time vehicle, route, stop, and arrival data for agencies that have puchased NextBus's hardware and/or software.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Proprietary (non-standard) vendor APIs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://api.citybik.es\">CityBikes</a> - REST API for aggregated bikeshare data from around the world. Powered by <a href=\"https://github.com/eskerda/pybikes\">pyBikes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/eskerda/pybikes\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">492</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":492,\"repo\":\"eskerda/pybikes\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Software for Creating APIs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://thetransitclock.org\">TransitClock</a> - Java application that can consume raw vehicle positions and generate prediction times in formats such as GTFS-realtime.  Formerly known as \"Transitime\".</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>On-line courses</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://olc.worldbank.org/content/introduction-general-transit-feed-specification-gtfs-and-informal-transit-system-mapping\">World Bank - \"Intro. to GTFS\" online course</a> - A free, online, self-paced course for learning about GTFS and GTFS-realtime.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Blog posts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mjskay/when-ish-is-my-bus\">When(ish) is my bus? Data and code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mjskay/when-ish-is-my-bus\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">43</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":43,\"repo\":\"mjskay/when-ish-is-my-bus\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The data and code (R) behind Whenish is my bus? Data includes three days of historical vehicle positions and the survey results.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Blog posts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://kurtraschke.com/2015/01/legacy-avl-export\">\"Legacy AVL system? It's okay, join the club.\" by Kurt Raschke</a> - Discussion of options for transforming legacy AVL system data into the GTFS-realtime format.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Blog posts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@sjbarbeau/whats-new-in-gtfs-realtime-v2-0-cd45e6a861e9\">\"What's new in GTFS-realtime v2.0\" by Sean Barbeau</a> - Discuss the shortfalls in GTFS-realtime v1.0 and the improvements in v2.0.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Blog posts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://transitdata.net/avl-cad-and-real-time-passenger-info-for-beginners/\">\"AVL, CAD, and Real-Time Passenger Info for Beginners\" by Tony Laidig</a> - Provides a general introduction to technology used to track vehicles.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Government reports</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.apta.com/resources/reportsandpublications/Documents/APTA-Embracing-Open-Data.pdf\">APTA Policy Development and Research - Public Transportation Embracing Open Data</a> - APTA's discussion of the benefits and challenges of open transit data (a short summary of the below TCRP report).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:32:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Getting started</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://olc.worldbank.org/content/introduction-general-transit-feed-specification-gtfs-and-informal-transit-system-mapping\">World Bank - \"Intro. to GTFS\" online course</a> - A free, online, self-paced course for learning about GTFS and GTFS-realtime.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T14:02:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"quozd/awesome-dotnet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Machine Learning and Data Science</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giacomelli/GeneticSharp\">GeneticSharp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/giacomelli/GeneticSharp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">999</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":999,\"repo\":\"giacomelli/GeneticSharp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Multi-platform genetic algorithm library for .NET Core and .NET Framework. The library has several implementations of GA operators, like: selection, crossover, mutation, reinsertion and termination.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-02T12:35:42.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1522627200000,"to":1522713599999,"previousId":"2018-04-03","nextId":"2018-04-01","nextName":"Apr 1st, 2018","previousName":"Apr 3rd, 2018"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}